{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"One of the problems of writing, and working, and looking at the Internet"},{"time":3000,"text":"is that it's very hard to separate fashion from deep change."},{"time":10000,"text":"And so, to start helping that, I want to take us back to 1835."},{"time":14000,"text":"In 1835, James Gordon Bennett founded the first mass-circulation newspaper"},{"time":21000,"text":"in New York City."},{"time":23000,"text":"And it cost about 500 dollars to start it,"},{"time":26000,"text":"which was about the equivalent of 10,000 dollars of today."},{"time":30000,"text":"By 15 years later, by 1850, doing the same thing"},{"time":34000,"text":"-- starting what was experienced as a mass--circulation daily paper"},{"time":37000,"text":"-- would come to cost two and a half million dollars."},{"time":41000,"text":"10,000, two and a half million, 15 years."},{"time":44000,"text":"That's the critical change that is being inverted by the Net."},{"time":51000,"text":"And that's what I want to talk about today,"},{"time":54000,"text":"and how that relates to the emergence of social production."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"Starting with newspapers, what we saw was high cost as an initial requirement"},{"time":65000,"text":"for making information, knowledge and culture, which led to a stark bifurcation"},{"time":71000,"text":"between producers -- who had to be able to raise financial capital,"},{"time":75000,"text":"just like any other industrial organization --"},{"time":79000,"text":"and passive consumers that could choose from a certain set of"},{"time":82000,"text":"things that this industrial model could produce."},{"time":87000,"text":"Now, the term \"information society,\" \"information economy,\""},{"time":90000,"text":"for a very long time has been used as the thing that comes after"},{"time":94000,"text":"the industrial revolution. But in fact, for purposes of understanding what's happening"},{"time":100000,"text":"today, that's wrong. Because for 150 years, we've had an information economy."},{"time":106000,"text":"It's just been industrial,"},{"time":108000,"text":"which means those who were producing had to have a way of raising money"},{"time":112000,"text":"to pay those two and a half million dollars, and later, more for the telegraph,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and the radio transmitter, and the television, and eventually the mainframe."},{"time":121000,"text":"And that meant they were market based, or they were government owned,"},{"time":124000,"text":"depending on what kind of system they were in. And this characterized and anchored"},{"time":129000,"text":"the way information and knowledge were produced for the next 150 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"Now, let me tell you a different story. Around June 2002,"},{"time":141000,"text":"the world of supercomputers had a bombshell."},{"time":145000,"text":"The Japanese had, for the first time, created the fastest supercomputer --"},{"time":149000,"text":"the NEC Earth Simulator -- taking the primary from the U.S.,"},{"time":152000,"text":"and about two years later -- this, by the way, is measuring the trillion floating-point"},{"time":156000,"text":"operations per second that the computer's capable of running --"},{"time":160000,"text":"sigh of relief: IBM [Blue Gene] has just edged ahead of the NEC Earth Simulator."},{"time":166000,"text":"All of this completely ignores the fact that throughout this period,"},{"time":170000,"text":"there's another supercomputer running in the world -- SETI@home."},{"time":174000,"text":"Four and a half million users around the world, contributing their"},{"time":178000,"text":"leftover computer cycles, whenever their computer isn't working,"},{"time":182000,"text":"by running a screen saver, and together sharing their resources to create"},{"time":189000,"text":"a massive supercomputer that NASA harnesses to analyze the data"},{"time":194000,"text":"coming from radio telescopes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198000,"text":"What this picture suggests to us is that we've got a radical change in the way"},{"time":205000,"text":"information production and exchange is capitalized. Not that it's become"},{"time":209000,"text":"less capital intensive -- that there's less money that's required"},{"time":212000,"text":"-- but that the ownership of this capital, the way the capitalization happens,"},{"time":217000,"text":"is radically distributed. Each of us, in these advanced economies,"},{"time":222000,"text":"has one of these, or something rather like it -- a computer."},{"time":227000,"text":"They're not radically different from routers inside the middle of the network."},{"time":232000,"text":"And computation, storage and communications capacity are in the hands of"},{"time":237000,"text":"practically every connected person -- and these are the basic physical"},{"time":243000,"text":"capital means necessary for producing information, knowledge and culture,"},{"time":248000,"text":"in the hands of something like 600 million to a billion people around the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254000,"text":"What this means is that for the first time since the industrial revolution,"},{"time":260000,"text":"the most important means, the most important components of the core"},{"time":266000,"text":"economic activities -- remember, we are in an information economy"},{"time":270000,"text":"-- of the most advanced economies, and there more than anywhere else,"},{"time":275000,"text":"are in the hands of the population at large. This is completely different than what we've"},{"time":279000,"text":"seen since the industrial revolution. So we've got communications and computation"},{"time":284000,"text":"capacity in the hands of the entire population,"},{"time":287000,"text":"and we've got human creativity, human wisdom, human experience"},{"time":292000,"text":"-- the other major experience, the other major input --"},{"time":295000,"text":"which unlike simple labor -- stand here turning this lever all day long --"},{"time":300000,"text":"is not something that's the same or fungible among people."},{"time":303000,"text":"Any one of you who has taken someone else's job, or tried to give yours"},{"time":306000,"text":"to someone else, no matter how detailed the manual, you cannot transmit"},{"time":312000,"text":"what you know, what you will intuit under a certain set of circumstances."},{"time":317000,"text":"In that we're unique, and each of us holds this critical input"},{"time":321000,"text":"into production as we hold this machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"What's the effect of this? So, the story that most people know"},{"time":330000,"text":"is the story of free or open source software."},{"time":334000,"text":"This is market share of Apache Web server"},{"time":337000,"text":"-- one of the critical applications in Web-based communications."},{"time":343000,"text":"In 1995, two groups of people said,"},{"time":347000,"text":"\"Wow, this is really important, the Web! We need a much better Web server!\""},{"time":351000,"text":"One was a motley collection of volunteers who just decided,"},{"time":355000,"text":"you know, we really need this, we should write one,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and what are we going to do with what --"},{"time":360000,"text":"well, we're gonna share it! And other people will be able to develop it."},{"time":362000,"text":"The other was Microsoft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"Now, if I told you that 10 years later, the motley crew of people, who didn't control"},{"time":369000,"text":"anything that they produced, acquired 20 percent of the market"},{"time":372000,"text":"and was the red line, it would be amazing! Right?"},{"time":375000,"text":"Think of it in minivans. A group of automobile"},{"time":378000,"text":"engineers on their weekends are competing with Toyota. Right?"},{"time":383000,"text":"But, in fact, of course, the story is it's the 70 percent,"},{"time":386000,"text":"including the major e-commerce site -- 70 percent of a critical application"},{"time":391000,"text":"on which Web-based communications and applications work is produced in this form, in"},{"time":397000,"text":"direct competition with Microsoft. Not in a side issue --"},{"time":401000,"text":"in a central strategic decision to try to capture a component of the Net."},{"time":408000,"text":"Software has done this in a way that's been very visible, because"},{"time":413000,"text":"it's measurable. But the thing to see is that this actually happens throughout the Web."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419000,"text":"So, NASA, at some point, did an experiment where they took images of Mars"},{"time":425000,"text":"that they were mapping, and they said, instead of having three or four"},{"time":429000,"text":"fully trained Ph.D.s doing this all the time, let's break it up into small components,"},{"time":434000,"text":"put it up on the Web, and see if people, using a very simple interface,"},{"time":438000,"text":"will actually spend five minutes here,"},{"time":440000,"text":"10 minutes there, clicking. After six months,"},{"time":444000,"text":"85,000 people used this to generate mapping at a"},{"time":449000,"text":"faster rate than the images were coming in, which was, quote,"},{"time":453000,"text":"\"practically indistinguishable from the markings of a fully-trained Ph.D.,\""},{"time":457000,"text":"once you showed it to a number of people and computed the average."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"Now, if you have a little girl, and she goes and writes to"},{"time":467000,"text":"-- well, not so little, medium little -- tries to do research on Barbie."},{"time":471000,"text":"And she'll come to Encarta, one of the main online encyclopedias."},{"time":475000,"text":"This is what you'll find out about Barbie. This is it, there's nothing more to the definition,"},{"time":481000,"text":"including, \"manufacturers\" -- plural -- \"now more commonly produce"},{"time":485000,"text":"ethnically diverse dolls, like this black Barbie.\" Which is vastly better"},{"time":489000,"text":"than what you'll find in the encyclopedia.com,"},{"time":492000,"text":"which is Barbie, Klaus. (Laughter)"},{"time":496000,"text":"On the other hand, if they go to Wikipedia, they'll find a genuine article"},{"time":501000,"text":"-- and I won't talk a lot about Wikipedia, because Jimmy Wales is here --"},{"time":504000,"text":"but roughly equivalent to what you would find in the Britannica, differently written,"},{"time":510000,"text":"including the controversies over body image and commercialization,"},{"time":514000,"text":"the claims about the way in which she's a good role model, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522000,"text":"Another portion is not only how content is produced, but how relevance is produced."},{"time":526000,"text":"The claim to fame of Yahoo! was, we hire people to look -- originally, not anymore"},{"time":530000,"text":"-- we hire people to look at websites and tell you --"},{"time":535000,"text":"if they're in the index, they're good. This, on the other hand, is what 60,000"},{"time":539000,"text":"passionate volunteers produce in the Open Directory Project,"},{"time":543000,"text":"each one willing to spend an hour or two on something they really care about,"},{"time":548000,"text":"to say, this is good. So, this is the Open Directory Project, with 60,000 volunteers,"},{"time":554000,"text":"each one spending a little bit of time, as opposed to a few hundred"},{"time":557000,"text":"fully paid employees. No one owns it, no one owns the output,"},{"time":562000,"text":"it's free for anyone to use and it's the output of people acting out of social"},{"time":567000,"text":"and psychological motivations to do something interesting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571000,"text":"This is not only outside of businesses. When you think of what is the critical innovation"},{"time":577000,"text":"of Google, the critical innovation is outsourcing the one most important thing --"},{"time":582000,"text":"the decision about what's relevant -- to the community of the Web as a whole,"},{"time":589000,"text":"doing whatever they want to do: so, page rank."},{"time":592000,"text":"The critical innovation here is instead of our engineers, or our people saying"},{"time":598000,"text":"which is the most relevant, we're going to go out and count what you,"},{"time":601000,"text":"people out there on the Web, for whatever reason -- vanity, pleasure --"},{"time":605000,"text":"produced links, and tied to each other. We're going to count those, and count them up."},{"time":611000,"text":"And again, here, you see Barbie.com, but also, very quickly,"},{"time":615000,"text":"Adiosbarbie.com, the body image for every size. A contested cultural object,"},{"time":620000,"text":"which you won't find anywhere soon on Overture, which is the classic"},{"time":624000,"text":"market-based mechanism: whoever pays the most is highest on the list."}]},{"cues":[{"time":629000,"text":"So, all of that is in the creation of content, of relevance, basic human expression."},{"time":634000,"text":"But remember, the computers were also physical. Just physical materials"},{"time":638000,"text":"-- our PCs -- we share them together. We also see this in wireless."},{"time":642000,"text":"It used to be wireless was one person owned the license, they transmitted in an"},{"time":648000,"text":"area, and it had to be decided whether they would be licensed or based on property."},{"time":653000,"text":"What we're seeing now is that computers and radios are becoming so sophisticated"},{"time":658000,"text":"that we're developing algorithms to let people own machines, like Wi-Fi devices,"},{"time":664000,"text":"and overlay them with a sharing protocol that would allow a community like this"},{"time":669000,"text":"to build its own wireless broadband network simply from the simple principle:"},{"time":675000,"text":"When I'm listening, when I'm not using, I can help you transfer your messages;"},{"time":681000,"text":"and when you're not using, you'll help me transfer yours."},{"time":684000,"text":"And this is not an idealized version. These are working models that at least in some"},{"time":689000,"text":"places in the United States are being implemented, at least for public security."}]},{"cues":[{"time":696000,"text":"If in 1999 I told you, let's build a data storage and retrieval system."},{"time":702000,"text":"It's got to store terabytes. It's got to be available 24 hours a day,"},{"time":705000,"text":"seven days a week. It's got to be available from anywhere in the world."},{"time":708000,"text":"It has to support over 100 million users at any given moment. It's got to"},{"time":712000,"text":"be robust to attack, including closing the main index, injecting malicious files,"},{"time":717000,"text":"armed seizure of some major nodes. You'd say that would take years."},{"time":722000,"text":"It would take millions. But of course, what I'm describing is P2P file sharing."},{"time":729000,"text":"Right? We always think of it as stealing music, but fundamentally,"},{"time":732000,"text":"it's a distributed data storage and retrieval system, where people,"},{"time":736000,"text":"for very obvious reasons, are willing to share their bandwidth and their"},{"time":740000,"text":"storage to create something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743000,"text":"So, essentially what we're seeing is the emergence of a fourth transactional"},{"time":747000,"text":"framework. It used to be that there were two primary dimensions along which"},{"time":753000,"text":"you could divide things. They could be market based, or non-market based;"},{"time":756000,"text":"they could be decentralized, or centralized."},{"time":758000,"text":"The price system was a market-based and decentralized system."},{"time":761000,"text":"If things worked better because you actually had somebody organizing them,"},{"time":765000,"text":"you had firms, if you wanted to be in the market -- or you had governments"},{"time":768000,"text":"or sometimes larger non-profits in the non-market."},{"time":771000,"text":"It was too expensive to have decentralized social production,"},{"time":776000,"text":"to have decentralized action in society. That was not about society itself."},{"time":783000,"text":"That was, in fact, economic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785000,"text":"But what we're seeing now is the emergence of this fourth system"},{"time":789000,"text":"of social sharing and exchange."},{"time":790000,"text":"Not that it's the first time that we do nice things to each other, or for each other,"},{"time":795000,"text":"as social beings. We do it all the time."},{"time":799000,"text":"It's that it's the first time that it's having major economic impact."},{"time":803000,"text":"What characterizes them is decentralized authority."},{"time":808000,"text":"You don't have to ask permission, as you do in a property-based system."},{"time":811000,"text":"May I do this? It's open for anyone to create and innovate and share,"},{"time":817000,"text":"if they want to, by themselves or with others,"},{"time":821000,"text":"because property is one mechanism of coordination."},{"time":823000,"text":"But it's not the only one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":825000,"text":"Instead, what we see are social frameworks for all of the critical things that we use"},{"time":830000,"text":"property and contract in the market: information flows to decide what are"},{"time":833000,"text":"interesting problems; who's available and good for something;"},{"time":837000,"text":"motivation structures -- remember, money isn't always the best motivator."},{"time":841000,"text":"If you leave a $50 check after dinner with friends,"},{"time":845000,"text":"you don't increase the probability of being invited back."},{"time":849000,"text":"And if dinner isn't entirely obvious, think of sex. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":855000,"text":"It also requires certain new organizational approaches."},{"time":858000,"text":"And in particular, what we've seen is task organization."},{"time":862000,"text":"You have to hire people who know what they're doing."},{"time":864000,"text":"You have to hire them to spend a lot of time."},{"time":867000,"text":"Now, take the same problem,"},{"time":869000,"text":"chunk it into little modules, and motivations become trivial."},{"time":873000,"text":"Five minutes, instead of watching TV?"},{"time":875000,"text":"Five minutes I'll spend just because it's interesting. Just because it's fun."},{"time":879000,"text":"Just because it gives me a certain sense of meaning, or, in places that are more"},{"time":883000,"text":"involved, like Wikipedia, gives me a certain set of social relations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889000,"text":"So, a new social phenomenon is emerging."},{"time":893000,"text":"It's creating, and it's most visible when we see it as a new form of competition."},{"time":898000,"text":"Peer-to-peer networks assaulting the recording industry;"},{"time":901000,"text":"free and open source software taking market share from Microsoft;"},{"time":905000,"text":"Skype potentially threatening traditional telecoms;"},{"time":909000,"text":"Wikipedia competing with online encyclopedias."},{"time":912000,"text":"But it's also a new source of opportunities for businesses."},{"time":915000,"text":"As you see a new set of social relations and behaviors emerging,"},{"time":921000,"text":"you have new opportunities. Some of them are toolmakers."},{"time":925000,"text":"Instead of building well-behaved appliances"},{"time":928000,"text":"-- things that you know what they'll do in advance --"},{"time":930000,"text":"you begin to build more open tools. There's a new set of values,"},{"time":933000,"text":"a new set of things people value."},{"time":936000,"text":"You build platforms for self-expression and collaboration."},{"time":940000,"text":"Like Wikipedia, like the Open Directory Project,"},{"time":944000,"text":"you're beginning to build platforms, and you see that as a model."},{"time":947000,"text":"And you see surfers, people who see this happening, and in some sense"},{"time":951000,"text":"build it into a supply chain, which is a very curious one. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":956000,"text":"You have a belief: stuff will flow out of connected human beings."},{"time":959000,"text":"That'll give me something I can use, and I'm going to contract with someone."},{"time":962000,"text":"I will deliver something based on what happens. It's very scary"},{"time":966000,"text":"-- that's what Google does, essentially."},{"time":968000,"text":"That's what IBM does in software services, and they've done reasonably well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972000,"text":"So, social production is a real fact, not a fad."},{"time":976000,"text":"It is the critical long-term shift caused by the Internet."},{"time":980000,"text":"Social relations and exchange become significantly more important than they ever"},{"time":987000,"text":"were as an economic phenomenon. In some contexts, it's even more efficient"},{"time":991000,"text":"because of the quality of the information, the ability to find the best person,"},{"time":996000,"text":"the lower transaction costs. It's sustainable and growing fast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000000,"text":"But -- and this is the dark lining -- it is threatened by"},{"time":1006000,"text":"-- in the same way that it threatens -- the incumbent industrial systems."},{"time":1010000,"text":"So next time you open the paper, and you see an intellectual property decision,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"a telecoms decision, it's not about something small and technical."},{"time":1021000,"text":"It is about the future of the freedom to be as social beings with each other,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"and the way information, knowledge and culture will be produced."},{"time":1032000,"text":"Because it is in this context that we see a battle over how easy or hard it will be"},{"time":1039000,"text":"for the industrial information economy to simply go on as it goes,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"or for the new model of production to begin to develop alongside that industrial model,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"and change the way we begin to see the world and report what it is that we see."},{"time":1054000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}